President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Oregon due to severe storms, flooding, landslides, and mudslides that occurred from February 5 to February 9, 2020. This declaration allows for Federal assistance to supplement State, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available for affected individuals in Umatilla County and the Confederated Tribes of the Umatilla Indian Reservation, which can include grants for temporary housing and home repairs, low-cost loans for uninsured property losses, and other recovery programs. Additionally, Federal funding will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures statewide. Dolph A. Diemont has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas, and further designations may be made based on damage assessments. Residents and business owners in the designated counties can apply for assistance online or by calling the provided toll-free telephone numbers. For further information, the FEMA News Desk can be contacted.